headline: TXN Q1 Earnings Call: Industrial Recovery and Tariff Risks Shape Outlook
summary: Analog chip manufacturer Texas Instruments (NASDAQ:TXN) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 11.1% year on year to $4.07 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $4.35 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $1.28 per share was 20.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
